cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.FL

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and rewrite rules. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields are closely related to NLP. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) as it deals with phonology and finite-state transducers.
